Headlines.Headline: Ameritech points finger at MediaOne, Time Warner 7-1-98

#text: Ameritech (AIT)
said Wednesday it's filed a complaint with the FCC charging MediaOne (UMG)
and Time Warner (TWX)

Cable with an "outrageous display of anti-competitive monopoly power." Ameritech
    says that when the two larger companies signed exclusive deals in the Detroit-Chicago
    region with Disney (DIS)

to carry Classic Sports Network, they did so in a deliberate effort to squeeze out
    Ameritech's Americast cable unit. Ameritech had carried the 24-hour cable channel since
    its 1995 inception, and will now be forced to drop it. "Unless the FCC intervenes,
    this will be a significant step backwards for thousands of our customers," said Deb
    Lenart, president of Ameritech New Media. Ameritech shares rose 1/16 to 44 15/16. MediaOne
    tacked on 7/16 to 44 3/8, while Time Warner added 3/4 to 86 3/16.
